description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a Junior Clinical Fellow in Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be based at the Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital, although you will be expected to work at any of the Trust’s sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post combines obstetrics and gynaecology and involves working in the junior registrar rota (1:9). The duties cover the full clinical range of Gynaecological and Obstetric procedures. Supervision is provided by consultants and senior registrars.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Motivated candidates will have the chance to gain experience in minimal access surgery, early pregnancy assessment, paediatric and adolescent gynaecology, human factors training and perinatal mental health. The training will be tailored on needs and special interests.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have full GMC registration with a licence to practise and MRCOG part 1.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department is within one of the most dynamic new university teaching hospitals in the country with excellent reputations in patient care and staff training/education. The directorate prides itself on its work environment and teamworking set within new facilities. Norfolk is a county with beautiful scenery, superb leisure facilities and excellent links to the rest of the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquiries please contact Mr Gautam Raje or Mr Ilias Giarensis on 01603 286286.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameIlias GiarenisJob titleConsultant GynaecologistEmail addressilias.giarenis@nnuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
